18/05/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Three ethnic Albanians have been arrested for burning a Serbian Orthodox church in Kosovo during the March riots, a UN police spokesman announced Monday (17 May).
The three men reportedly have confessed to torching the Bogorodica Ljeviska church in Prizren.
Also Monday, the Serbian coalition Return announced that it has completed work on a report about the situation in Kosovo following the riots.
It includes measures both the government and UNMIK should take to avert more violence.
(AFP, B92, Tanjug - 17/05/04)
